cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with sequence modeling tasks such as language understanding and machine translation. Additionally, the paper proposes a new self-attentive recurrent sequence model that improves upon existing models in these tasks. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the proposed model is a neural network architecture and the paper discusses its training and performance on various tasks. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a new model that combines the strengths of existing models and improves upon them in various tasks. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the proposed model is a neural network architecture and the paper discusses its design and implementation. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with visual data, but the proposed model could potentially be applied to sequence modeling tasks in computer vision.
